<H1>Installing AugXml</H1>
<H2>Getting AugXml</H2>
<P>The AugXml program is part of the <A HREF="http://hyperscope.org/">HyperScope</A>
project. There has not been a stable release yet, but you can
download the latest source code from the <A HREF="http://blueoxen.net/c/hyperscope/wiki.pl?Download">AugXml</A>
Subversion repository.</P>
<HR>
<H2>System Requirements</H2>
<P>In order to run the AugXml program, you will need Java 5. You can
download a <A HREF="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp">JRE</A>
from the Java site at Sun.</P>
<P>To compile, there are some additional requirements. You will need
the following:</P>
<UL>
	<LI><P><A HREF="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp">JDK 5</A>
	– older versions of Java (i.e. 1.4.x) are not sufficient.</P>
	<LI><P><A HREF="http://ant.apache.org/">Ant 1.7</A> or newer - this
	is not yet released, so you will need to download a <A HREF="http://cvs.apache.org/snapshots/ant/">nightly</A>
	build from apache and build it yourself.</P>
	<LI><P><A HREF="http://www.junit.org/">JUnit</A> 4 – this version
	of JUnit requires JDK 5 and Ant 1.7 or newer.</P>
</UL>
